Boil a full #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} for Mincing (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} on high heat
with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Add the @Macaroni{180%g} to the water and bring back to
the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}.
Drizzle with @olive oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together. Set
aside.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{90%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot,
add the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90%g}. Stir fry until golden,
~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Next, stir in the garlic until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @Water for the Sauce{50%ml}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g} and cooked
pasta to the pan. Bring to the boil, stirring constantly, then remove from the
heat.

Vigorously stir the @Creme Fraiche{150%g}, @Dijon Mustard{10%g} and both the
grated Cheddar and @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g} into the macaroni.
Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add a splash of water if it's a little
too thick. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Share the bacon mac & cheese between your #bowls{}. Sprinkle over the
@Chilli Flakes{1%pinch}.

> Add less chilli flakes if you'd prefer things milder.

Serve the @Baby Leaf Mix{50%g} alongside and drizzle over the
@Balsamic Glaze{12%ml} and a little @olive oil{}. Enjoy!